Introduction

Are you passionate about data? And is your interest not limited to analysis alone? Then we are looking for you to join our Analytics & AI team!

What will you do?

Together with your colleagues, you will help our clients find answers to complex challenges and ensure they can always make the right decisions. In a team of data scientists and other data specialists, your role is to develop and implement effective strategies to access and structure data.

You’ll also use your knowledge, experience, and hands-on mentality to support colleagues in developing sustainable and reliable scripts and models for processing data, and you’ll deploy them to the cloud for production. 🚀🚀




What do you bring to the table?

You have a higher professional or academic education level;
You have 3 years of experience in a similar role (experience in a client-facing role is a plus);
You are highly analytical, able to advise clients at a strategic level, and skilled at turning complex challenges into practical, results-driven solutions;
You enjoy having freedom in your work. You are proactive, feel responsible for the success of your clients, have a practical mindset, and are not afraid to dive into the unknown;
You like mentoring junior team members and sharing your knowledge and experience with them;
You have experience with Python and databases (e.g., SQL), ETL tooling, Azure and/or Google Cloud Platform, and are always looking for better tools, techniques, and opportunities to further develop your skills;
You are experienced in unlocking and structuring raw data and translating it into relevant insights for clients;
You have experience developing data pipelines, algorithms, and machine learning models.

